
[1]hippomane

   HIP'POMANE, n. [Gr. a horse, and madness.]

   1. A sort of poisonous substance, used anciently as a philter or
   love-charm.

   2. In botany, the manchineel-tree, which abounds with a milky juice
   which is acrid, caustic and poisonous.
